Los Alvarez first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusTX/> Prior to the [[2010 U.S. census]] 4 CDPs ([[Barrera, Texas|Barrera]], [[El Quiote, Texas|El Quiote]], [[Flor del Rio, Texas|Flor del Rio]], and [[Palo Blanco, Texas|Palo Blanco]]) were carved out from its territory.<ref name=2010CensusTX/>

